VALUES
(44, 13, 41, 23, 28, 14, 22, 'ye despisers, and wonder, and perish', 'Judgment and Unbelief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of scorn and disbelief. Acts 13:41 warns of perishing due to disbelief, paralleling Isaiah 28:14-22''s call to heed the Lord''s word against mockers. This connection highlights the theme of judgment for those who reject divine revelation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 41, 20, 5, 12, 12, 'despisers', 'Despisers and Instruction', 'This connection highlights the theme of despising wisdom and instruction. Both passages address the consequences of rejecting guidance and the resulting peril.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 41, 40, 21, 41, 44, 'ye shall in no wise believe', 'Rejection and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection and its dire consequences. Both passages emphasize the idea of disbelief leading to destruction and the transfer of God''s favor to others.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 42, 44, 28, 28, 28, 'the Gentiles besought that these words', 'Gentile Reception of Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of Gentiles seeking salvation. In both passages, the Gentiles express a desire to hear the message of God, emphasizing their openness to salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 42, 26, 3, 6, 6, 'these words might be preached to them', 'Gentiles Seeking God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of Gentiles desiring to hear God''s message. In Acts, the Gentiles ask to hear the words preached, paralleling Ezekiel''s mention of people who would listen if sent to them.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 42, 40, 11, 21, 21, 'these words might be preached to them', 'Response to Preaching and Repentance', 'This connection highlights the response of the Gentiles in Acts seeking the message, paralleling the unrepentant cities in Matthew. Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing and responding to the message of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 42, 40, 19, 30, 30, NULL, 'First and Last Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of inclusion, where the Gentiles, often seen as the last, seek the message of salvation. In Matthew, the reversal of status is emphasized, suggesting that those who are last will be prioritized.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 42, 44, 10, 33, 33, 'that these words might be preached to them', 'Gentile Interest in God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the eagerness of Gentiles to hear God''s message. Both passages emphasize the desire of Gentiles to receive teachings about God, as seen in their requests to hear more.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 43, 44, 11, 23, 23, 'grace of God', 'Connection of Grace and Exhortation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of grace and encourage believers to remain steadfast in their faith. Acts 13:43 speaks of continuing in the grace of God, while Acts 11:23 highlights the joy of witnessing the grace of God and encourages cleaving to the Lord.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 43, 44, 14, 22, 22, 'continue in the grace of God', 'Encouragement to Continue in Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of perseverance in faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of continuing in the grace of God and the faith amidst challenges.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 43, 45, 3, 24, 24, 'continue in the grace of God', 'Connection of Grace and Justification', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of grace, with Acts 13:43 encouraging believers to continue in the grace of God, while Romans 3:24 speaks of being justified freely by his grace. This connection highlights the importance of grace in the process of salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 43, 45, 5, 2, 2, 'continue in the grace of God', 'Connection of Grace in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of grace, with Acts highlighting the encouragement to continue in the grace of God, while Romans speaks of standing in grace through faith. This connection highlights the importance of grace in the believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 43, 47, 5, 11, 11, 'persuaded them to continue', 'Persuasion in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the act of persuasion in ministry. In Acts, Paul and Barnabas persuade the followers to continue in grace, while in 2 Corinthians, Paul speaks of persuading men in light of the Lord''s terror.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 43, 47, 6, 1, 1, 'grace of God', 'Connection of Grace in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of ''grace of God.'' Acts 13:43 encourages believers to continue in this grace, while 2 Corinthians 6:1 warns against receiving it in vain. This connection highlights the ongoing significance of grace in the believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 43, 48, 5, 1, 1, 'continue in the grace of God', 'Grace and Freedom Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace and liberty in the Christian faith. In Acts, Paul and Barnabas encourage believers to continue in the grace of God, while Galatians emphasizes standing firm in the freedom Christ provides.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 44, 1, 49, 10, 10, NULL, 'Gathering of the People', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of people to hear God''s word. In Acts, the whole city comes together to hear the message, while Genesis speaks of the gathering of people to Shiloh, indicating a significant moment of unity and expectation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 44, 19, 110, 3, 3, 'the whole city together to hear', 'Willingness to Hear God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of people gathering to hear God''s message. Both passages emphasize a collective willingness and eagerness in the presence of divine power and holiness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 44, 23, 11, 10, 10, 'the whole city together to hear', 'Gathering of the Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the gathering of people to hear the word of God in Acts, paralleling the prophecy in Isaiah about the Gentiles seeking the root of Jesse. Both passages emphasize a significant moment of unity and interest from diverse groups in the message of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 44, 23, 60, 8, 8, 'whole city together to hear', 'Gathering to Hear the Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of people gathering to receive a message. In Acts, the whole city comes together to hear the word of God, while Isaiah speaks of people flying to their windows, suggesting a desire to receive something important.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 45, 65, 1, 10, 10, NULL, 'Envy and Speaking Evil', 'This connection highlights the theme of speaking against others out of envy or ignorance. Both passages emphasize the act of speaking evil, whether motivated by jealousy or a lack of understanding.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 45, 44, 18, 6, 6, 'blaspheming', 'Opposition and Blasphemy Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition faced by Paul, with the Jews expressing envy and blasphemy in Acts 13:45 and Paul responding to similar blasphemy in Acts 18:6. This connection highlights the recurring theme of resistance to the message of the Gospel.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 45, 44, 5, 17, 17, NULL, 'Indignation and Envy in Opposition', 'This connection highlights the emotional responses of the Jewish leaders in both passages. In Acts 13:45, the Jews are ''filled with envy,'' while in Acts 5:17, the high priest and his associates are ''filled with indignation,'' showcasing a common theme of opposition to the apostles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 45, 52, 2, 16, 16, 'filled with envy', 'Envy and Opposition to Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition faced by Paul and the early Christians from the Jews. Acts 13:45 highlights the Jews'' envy and blasphemy against Paul''s message, while 1 Thessalonians 2:16 speaks of their efforts to prevent Gentiles from being saved.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 45, 40, 27, 18, 18, 'filled with envy', 'Envy Leading to Conflict', 'Both passages emphasize the role of envy in provoking actions against others. In Acts, the Jews'' envy leads them to contradict Paul, while in Matthew, envy motivates the delivery of Jesus to be crucified.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 45, 46, 3, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Envy and Strife', 'This connection highlights the theme of envy present in both passages. Acts 13:45 describes the Jews'' envy leading to strife against Paul, while 1 Corinthians 3:3 addresses the resulting divisions and strife among believers due to envy.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 45, 60, 4, 4, 4, NULL, 'Envy and Speaking Evil', 'This connection highlights the theme of envy leading to speaking evil. In both passages, individuals react negatively to others'' actions, expressing their discontent through blasphemy or speaking evil.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 46, 44, 28, 28, 28, 'we turn to the Gentiles', 'Salvation for the Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize the outreach to the Gentiles after the rejection by the Jews. Paul and Barnabas declare their intention to turn to the Gentiles, while the later passage confirms that the salvation of God is sent to them.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 46, 40, 21, 43, 43, 'judge yourselves unworthy of everlasting life', 'Rejection and New Recipients', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of the original audience and the subsequent offer of God''s message to others. Acts 13:46 speaks of turning to the Gentiles after the Jews judged themselves unworthy, paralleling Matthew 21:43''s declaration of the kingdom being given to a different nation.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 46, 44, 18, 5, 6, 'judge yourselves unworthy of everlasting life', 'Paul''s Ministry to the Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s decision to turn to the Gentiles after facing opposition from the Jews. In each instance, he declares that the Jews have judged themselves unworthy of everlasting life, leading him to focus on the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 46, 45, 2, 10, 10, NULL, 'Order of Gospel Proclamation', 'Both passages emphasize the priority of the Jews in receiving the word of God. Acts 13:46 highlights the necessity of speaking to the Jews first, while Romans 2:10 states that glory is given to the Jew first, indicating a consistent theme of the Jewish priority in the gospel message.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
